Mac And Cheese

- 2 lb cheese (3:1 mix of cheddar and gruy√®re works great)
Preheat oven to 400F.
Grate the cheese.

- 1 lb box of sauce-trapping pasta, such as shells or elbows
Cook pasta in salted water, 2 minutes less than the package recommends.

- 2 Tbsp butter
Drain pasta, toss with butter until evenly coated.

- 3 cups water
- 20g sodium citrate
+ cheese
In a large saucepan, bring the water to a bare simmer.
Whisk in the sodium citrate until dissolved.
Add grated cheese a little at a time.
Use an immersion blender to mix the sauce completely uniformly.

- 1 tsp hot sauce (e.g. Franks or Sriracha)
- 1/2 tsp mustard powder
- 1/4 tsp garlic powder
- salt
Add hot sauce, mustard powder and garlic powder to cheese sauce. Taste and add salt as needed.

Mix pasta into cheese sauce.
Mix until very well combined and no more air bubbles appear.

- 1.5 cups panko breadcrumbs
- 4.5 Tbsp butter
- salt
Melt butter. Evenly mix panko and butter and a pinch of salt in small bowl.

Spray a 9x13 baking dish.
Scrape pasta and sauce into dish and smooth the surface.
Scatter topping evenly.
Bake for about 45 minutes until topping is nicely brown and sauce is bubbling.

Allow to rest for 15 minutes before serving.